      <bioghist id="aspace_a01afd71770d3fa857b3310781c01477">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Arthur Graham is the proprietor of Polyglot Press in Lexington, KY. "Graham [is] a former tenor with the Metropolitan Opera and now a professor of Music at the University of Kentucky. Prof. Graham began printing in New York and continued in Pennsylvania and Florida before moving to Lexington. Printing as the Polyglot Press, he has brought fine typographic treatment to works in various languages. He has printed in Danish, in English, in French, in German, in Hebrew, in Latin, in Neapolitan, in Spanish, and in Yiddish, and his work demonstrates a sensitive appreciation for linguistic nuance. In addition to the variety of languages in which he prints, Arthur Graham also has assembled an enviable array of type fonts, allowing him to bring further suggestions of meaning and mood to the way in which his words are displayed."</p>
         <p>Reference: Burton Milward, "<ref actuate="onrequest"
                 href="http://www.uky.edu/Libraries/klp/papers/milward1992/ "
                 linkrole="text/html"
                 show="new">The Private Press Tradition in Lexington, Kentucky</ref>," in <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>The Kentucky Review</part>
            </title>, Volume XI, Number 3, Autumn 1992, pp. 5-27. Copyright © 1992 by the University of Kentucky Libraries.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_b7bfc25f5d36262753a10123e7a43564">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains a selection of works printed by Polyglot Press, many of which reproduce illustrations by Fritz Kredel (1900-1973), a German graphic designer and illustrator active in the United States. Many of these published works also have individual catalog records in <ref actuate="onrequest"
                 href="http://orbis.library.yale.edu/vwebv/"
                 linkrole="text/html"
                 show="new">Orbis</ref>.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_3e9e951bc170b9eb8c5b62b627b9afb2">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into three series: I. Bound Volumes, 2002-2011. II. Prints, 1970-2013. III. Correspondence &amp; Ephemera, undated.</p>  
      </arrangement>
